I"Í<p>The Mobile App integration allows Home Assistant mobile apps to easily integrate with Home Assistant.</p>
<p>If you are planning to use a mobile application that integrates with Home Assistant, we recommend that you keep this integration enabled.</p>
<p>If you are a mobile app developer, see the <a href="https://developers.home-assistant.io/docs/en/app_integration_index.html">developer documentation</a> for instructions on how to build your app on top of the mobile app component.</p>
<h2>Configuration</h2>
<p>This integration is by default enabled, unless youâ€™ve disabled or removed the <a href="https://www.home-assistant.io/integrations/default_config/"><code>default_config:</code></a> line from your configuration. If that is the case, the following example shows you how to enable this integration manually:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Example configuration.yaml entry
mobile_app:
</code></pre>
